The paper deals with algorithms and data structures for graph problems, specifically the problem of designing sparse fault-tolerant approximate shortest path trees and the related problem of updating a minimum spanning forest after a batch of edge modifications. This falls under the scope of computer science sub-categories such as data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and game theory (cs.GT).
